<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Hungary-RFE     03-06 0122</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Hungary-RFE,0125</SECOND>
<HEAD>Radio Free Europe Allowed To Base Reporter In Hungary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A correspondent for the U.S.
government-funded Radio Free Europe broadcast network will be
permitted to work in Hungary without any restrictions, Hungarian
radio reported.
   That would make Hungary the first Soviet bloc country to accredit
an RFE reporter. Two years ago, only journalists from East European
countries were allowed as permanent correspondents based in Budapest.
   RFE, headquartered in Munich, West Germany, broadcasts in all
east European languages and has frequently been the target of strong
attacks by Soviet bloc governments and newspapers.
   According to the Hungarian radio broadcast Sunday, 18 Western
correspondents work in Budapest and 12 other applications have been
submitted to the Foreign Ministry.
</TEXT>
