   Royal Riley, a former Daily News reporter who
later served as an assistant district attorney in Queens, died
Friday at the age of 82 of complications from emphysema.
   Riley worked for the Queens Evening News, the Long Island Press
and the Daily News, which he left in 1955 after more than 25 years
of service.
   He earned a law degree from St. John's University in 1927 and
served in the Queens district attorney's office under three
administrations from 1955 to 1979.
