<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--MovieHouses     03-06 0177</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Movie Houses,0179</SECOND>
<HEAD>NYC To Buy Out Leases On Sleazy Block To Speed Cleanup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   City officials hope to close a pornographic movie
house and six other theaters along a sleazy strip of West 42nd
Street around the corner from Times Square by buying out their
leases, according to a report published today.
   The conversion is part of the long-delayed plan by the city and
state to clean up the crime-ridden block with office towers, arts
facilities and a merchandise mart.
   New York Newsday said it learned that the board of the Public
Development Corp. is scheduled to vote March 22 on a tentative
agreement in which the city would pay about $2 million for leases on
the theaters.
   The city had planned to seek control of the property through
condemnation proceedings because the leases have 71 years to run.
But officials said that by buying out the leases, the city will get
control of the theaters sooner and be able to convert them to such
uses as drama and dance rehearsal halls.
