<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Israel-Shooting     03-06 0148</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Israel-Shooting,0155</SECOND>
<HEAD>6-Year-Old Boy Kills Taxi Driver in Handgun Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 6-year-old playing with his father's handgun
Monday shot and killed a taxi driver, a news agency reported.
   The child was waving his father's 9mm pistol outside the window
of his family car when the gun went off, fatally wounding taxi
driver Zecharia Krobim, 53, of Ashkelon, in the head, the Itim news
agency said.
   The father and son were not identified, and the father was
charged with negligence, Itim said.
   The father said he did not realize his son had removed the pistol
from a front-seat compartment, the agency reported.
   When the child was questioned by police, all he said was, ``I was
playing with the gun, I was playing with the gun.''
   The agency said the shooting occurred in the parking lot of
Kaplan hospital in the Tel Aviv suburb of Rehovot.
</TEXT>
