<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Nicaragua-Crash     03-06 0120</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Nicaragua-Crash,0124</SECOND>
<HEAD>Buses Plunge, Killing 2 Military Recruits and Injuring 30</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANAGUA, Nicaragua (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two buses en route to a military school
plunged over a precipice, killing two young recruits and injuring
more than 30, officials said Monday.
   The accident occurred Sunday morning in the province of
Matagalpa, about 85 miles north of Managua, the daily El Nuevo
Diario said.
   It said the recruits were on their way to a military training
school at Mulukukuu in Jinotega province near the Honduran border.
   A Defense Ministry spokesman said by telephone the injured were
taken to a hospital in Matagalpa, a Defense Ministry spokesman said.
   Military service in Nicaragua is mandatory for men between the
ages of 18 and 25.
