<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Avalanche     03-06 0159</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Avalanche,0164</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two More Die in Avalanche in French Alps</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GRENOBLE, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An avalanche in the French Alps on Monday
killed two men, including a ski instructor, who were skiing off the
trail near the Val d'Isere resort, police said.
   The instructor, Georges Simon, and an unidentified companion were
killed in the avalanche near Tignes, eight miles from the Val
d'Isere ski resort, police in Grenoble said.
   A third man was hospitalized in critical condition, said the
police official, who spoke on condition of anonymity.
   A woman skiing with the group was found uninjured about 10
minutes after the avalanche by rescue workers who saw her ski
sticking through the snow, police said.
   The group had been off trail and was ignoring elementary safety
rules, police said.
   Seven avalanches reported over the weekend left two skiers dead
and dozens injured. French authorities have advised skiers to stay
on the alpine trails, especially during the warm afternoons.
