<FIRST>r i AM-Taiwan-China     03-06 0178</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Taiwan-China,0183</SECOND>
<HEAD>Taiwanese Freighter Reportedly Seized By Mainland China</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Chinese patrol boat has seized a
Taiwanese freighter with 31 crew members aboard, the freighter's
owner said Sunday.
   The 1,963-ton Kuang Ta No. 2, loaded with scrap metal and used
paper, was forced to sail to China on Friday, shortly after leaving
Hong Kong for the southern Taiwan port of Kaohsiung, said Tsai
Fu-chuan, general manager of Kuang Hwa Steam Ship Company.
   ``The freighter was sailing on the right route. We don't know why
it was seized,'' Tsai said.
   Tsai quoted his agency in Hong Kong as saying the freighter was
taken to Zuhai in southern China's Guangdong province. He said the
crew and the freighter were in good condition and hoped they would
be released soon.
   Zuhai freighter port officials were unavailable for comment
Sunday.
   The governments in Taiwan and mainland China both claim to be the
legitimate ruler of all China. The Nationalist government fled to
Taiwan in 1949 upon losing a civil war to the Communist forces on
mainland China.
</TEXT>
