<HEAD>Mixed Weekend Weather Mirrored In Crop Markets</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wheat futures prices opened mostly higher but corn
and soybeans were mostly lower this morning on the Chicago Board of
Trade, reflecting a mixed bag of weather in key growing areas over
the weekend.
   Some expected precipitation did not materialize in the winter
wheat regions of the Great Plains, boosting wheat futures prices,
particularly those for wheat to be harvested this spring.
   But rain and snow fell in much of the Midwest over the weekend,
dampening buying interest in corn and soybean futures.
