<FIRST>r f AM-USX-Quebec     03-06 0141</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-USX-Quebec,0147</SECOND>
<HEAD>USX Sells Outstanding Shares of Quebec Cartier Mining</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   USX Holdings Inc., a wholly owned subsidiary of
USX Corp., said Monday it has agreed to sell Quebec Cartier Mining
Co. and some associated companies. The price was not disclosed.
   Quebec Cartier operates iron ore mines and iron ore processing
facilities in Quebec.
   Dofasco Inc. will buy 25 percent of the outstanding shares of
Quebec Cartier and the associated corporations and has agreed to buy
2 million tons of iron ore pellets a year from Quebec Cartier
beginning in April 1990, according to a definitive agreement.
   USX Holdings said it has signed a letter of intent to sell the
remaining 75 percent of the oustanding shares to Elders Resources
North America. This transaction is subject to completion of
definitive agreements and approval of both boards of directors.
</TEXT>
