<FIRST>r f AM-CarThefts     03-06 0142</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Car Thefts,0147</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Companies Agree To Offer Anti-Theft Discounts</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two insurance companies announced Monday they
plan to offer 5 percent discounts to motorists who agree to let
police stop their cars if they are seen on the road between 1 a.m.
and 5 a.m.
   The program is designed to deter the theft of cars during the
four-hour period, which is prime time for thefts.
   A police decal on a side window of the cars identifies them as
participants in the program, which is already in effect in New York
City, Yonkers, East Brunswick, N.J., and Philadelphia.
   The Fireman's Fund Insurance Cos. and Travelers Insurance Co.
said the discounts will be offered on comprehensive car policies if
the customer participates in the Combat Auto Theft program and if
the reductions are approved by the state Insurance Department.
</TEXT>
