<HEAD>Shultz Named To Boeing Board</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEATTLE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Secretary of State George Shultz has been
elected to the board of directors of Boeing Co., the Seattle-based
aerospace company said Monday.
   Shultz, 68, now professor of international economics in the
graduate school of business at Stanford University, becomes the 13th
member of Boeing's board.
   He was secretary of state from July 1982 until former President
Ronald Reagan left office in January.
   Shultz is an honorary fellow of the Hoover Institution at
Stanford. He also is a director of Chevron Corp., General Motors
Corp. and Bechtel Group Inc.
